sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Browser (Client)
    participant Gateway as Home Gateway/Router
    participant Resolver as DNS Resolver (ISP)
    participant DNS as DNS Root/TLD/Auth Servers
    participant Backbone as Internet Backbone
    participant WebServer as Web Server

    Note over User, Resolver: Phase 1: DNS Resolution
    User->>User: Check Browser/OS Cache
    User->>Gateway: Recursive DNS Query
    Gateway->>Resolver: Forward Query (Port 53)

    loop Hierarchical Lookup
        Resolver->>DNS: Query Root/TLD/Authoritative
        DNS-->>Resolver: Referral or IP Address
    end

    Resolver-->>Gateway: Return IP Address
    Gateway-->>User: Return IP Address to Browser

    Note over User, WebServer: Phase 2: Web Page Request
    User->>Gateway: HTTP/HTTPS Request
    Gateway->>Backbone: Route Packets via ISP
    Backbone->>Backbone: Core Router Hops
    Backbone->>WebServer: Deliver Request to IP

    WebServer->>Backbone: Send HTML/Data Response
    Backbone->>Gateway: Route Back to Client IP
    Gateway->>User: Render Webpage
